  "text": "Our task is to show that the spectrum of (7.1) lies in the upper complex half plane {Im z > 0} if e = 0; and that it has a simple eigenvalue at zero and all the other eigenvalues lie in the upper complex half plane if e = 0. While this analysis is standard in the case when I is a selfadjoint operator (then the imaginary part of (7.1) is just P e Iδ(L 0 − e)IP e , manifestly a non-negative operator; see e.g. [CITATION_1] ), it needs some more thought in our case, where the interaction is non-selfadjoint. Let",
